Class HDBOfficer

java.lang.Object
BTO_Management_System.User
BTO_Management_System.Applicant
BTO_Management_System.HDBOfficer
public class HDBOfficer extends Applicant
Represents an HDB Officer, who can register to handle BTO projects, manage enquiries for their assigned project, and book flats for successful applicants. This class extends Applicant and implements various interfaces such as ProjectApplicant, Enquirer, EnquiryViewer, ProjectRegistrationRequester, and BookingOfficer.

    • isEligibleToApply

      protected boolean isEligibleToApply(BTOProject project)
      Checks if this HDB officer is eligible to apply for a given project as a regular applicant. Officers cannot apply for a project they have registered to handle. Eligibility is also based on the project's visibility, the officer's existing applications, age, and marital status, according to the project's flat type availability.
      Overrides:
      isEligibleToApply in class Applicant
      Parameters:
      project - The BTOProject to check eligibility for.
      Returns:
      true if the officer is eligible to apply, false otherwise.

    • register

      public void register(BTO_Management_System.ProjectViewable project)
      Registers this HDB officer to handle a specific BTO project. This creates a new RegistrationApplication and associates it with the officer and the project. The registration is pending approval from the project's manager.
      Parameters:
      project - The ProjectViewable to register for. Must be an instance of BTOProject.

    • bookFlat

      public void bookFlat(Application application, FlatType selectedFlatType)
      Books a flat of a specified type for a successful application in the project being handled by this officer. This updates the application status to 'BOOKED' and decrements the remaining units of the flat type in the project.
      Parameters:
      application - The Application to book the flat for. Must have a status of ApplicationStatus.SUCCESSFUL.
      selectedFlatType - The FlatType to be booked.

    • generateReceipt

      Parameters:
      application - The Application for which to generate the receipt. Must have a status of ApplicationStatus.BOOKED.

    • handleViewHandlingProjectEnquiry

      public void handleViewHandlingProjectEnquiry(Scanner scanner)
      Handles the UI interaction to view a specific enquiry for the handling project. It first checks if the officer is assigned to a project and if there are any enquiries. If so, it prompts the officer to enter the enquiry ID and displays the enquiry details using viewHandlingProjectEnquiry(int) if a valid ID is entered.
      Parameters:
      scanner - The Scanner object to read user input.

    • handleReplyHandlingProjectEnquiry

      public void handleReplyHandlingProjectEnquiry(Scanner scanner)
      Handles the UI interaction to reply to a specific enquiry for the handling project. It checks for project assignment and existing enquiries, then prompts the officer for the enquiry ID and the reply text. The reply is sent using replyHandlingProjectEnquiry(int, String) if a valid ID is provided.
      Parameters:
      scanner - The Scanner object to read user input.

    • handleBookFlat

      public void handleBookFlat(Scanner scanner)
      Handles the UI interaction to book a flat for a successful applicant in the handling project. It displays the list of successful applications and prompts the officer to enter the Application ID and the flat type to book. The booking is processed using bookFlat(Application, FlatType).
      Parameters:
      scanner - The Scanner object to read user input.

    • handleGenerateReceipt

      public void handleGenerateReceipt(Scanner scanner)
      Handles the UI interaction to generate a receipt for a booked flat. It displays the list of booked applications and prompts the officer to enter the Application ID for which to generate the receipt. The receipt is generated using generateReceipt(Application).
      Parameters:
      scanner - The Scanner object to read user input.

    • handleRegister

      public void handleRegister(Scanner scanner)
      Handles the UI interaction for an officer to register to handle a BTO project. It prompts the officer to enter the name of the project they wish to register for and calls the register(ProjectViewable) method to process the registration. Eligibility to register is checked beforehand.
      Parameters:
      scanner - The Scanner object to read user input.

    • handleViewRegistrationStatus

      public void handleViewRegistrationStatus()
      Handles the UI interaction to view the registration status of the officer for handling a project. It retrieves and displays the registration status using getRegistrationStatus() and provides details of the registered project and registration ID if a registration exists.
